        "description": {
            "value": "<p>As a scholar, you know all too well the importance of a sound mind. Thus, you attended a school—like the Farseer Tower or the Stone of the Seers—that taught the arts of befuddling lesser minds with figments and illusions or implanted sensations and memories.</p>\n<p><strong>Curriculum</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>cantrips:</strong> daze, figment</li>\n<li><strong>1st:</strong> dizzying colors, sleep, sure strike</li>\n<li><strong>2nd:</strong> illusory creature, stupefy</li>\n<li><strong>3rd:</strong> dream message, mind reading</li>\n<li><strong>4th:</strong> nightmare, vision of death</li>\n<li><strong>5th:</strong> hallucination, illusory scene</li>\n<li><strong>6th:</strong> never mind, phantasmal calamity</li>\n<li><strong>7th:</strong> project image, warp mind</li>\n<li><strong>8th:</strong> disappearance, uncontrollable dance</li>\n<li><strong>9th:</strong> phantasmagoria</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>School Spells</strong> initial: charming push; advanced: invisibility cloak</p>"
